
This module helps with some token management functions. You can
easily save delete and list tokens for which you have          
permissions saved in the Auth appliance you specify. Retrieved 
tokens can be saved to file, or to the profiles folder for use 
in authentication in this and other jsRiffleUtils modules.   

Usage: node token_getter.js [options]

Options: 
    -h, --help - Show this dialogue
    -p, --profile [domain] - Authenticate using a saved profile corresponding to the domain.
    -e, --env - Authenticate using the enviroment variables EXIS_DOMAIN and EXIS_TOKEN.
    -d, --delete - Delete the token from the specified Auth Appliance.
    -l, --list - List the tokens belonging to the specified domain from the specified Auth Appliance.
    -s, --save - Save the token as a profile that you can use for later authentication with the -p flag.
    -f, --file [/path/to/file] - Save the token to the specified file.
